sql:
SELECT workstation_name
FROM workstations
WHERE last_checked_in > 1555029373276;

external_knowledge:
- A job is considered to have been "accessed" if there is at least one entry in the 'access_logs' table referencing it;
- The 'submit_time' refers to the time when the job was initially submitted, based on the Java epoch time;
- The "earliest recorded submission time in their history" refers to the earliest 'submit_time' found in the 'job_history' table for each job.

One month is assumed to be 31 days for simplicity; 
2678400 seconds is equivalent to 31 days; 
Java epoch is the number of seconds since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 GMT.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS SuccessfulJobsWithoutRetries
FROM jobs
WHERE status = 'success' AND retries = 0;

SELECT js.status, COUNT(*) AS job_count
FROM jobs js
INNER JOIN workstations ws ON js.submitter_id = ws.workstation_id
WHERE js.created_at BETWEEN (
    SELECT MIN(created_at) FROM jobs
) AND (
    SELECT MAX(created_at) FROM jobs
)
GROUP BY js.status;
